			<article class="posts_listing post-2213 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-feature tag-christ tag-god tag-new tag-new-year tag-teach tag-teacher tag-umi" id="post-2213">
				
						
					<a href="http://www.umiteacher.com/a-new-year-to-seek-god-in-christian-education/" title="A New Year to Seek God in Christian Education" class="imgborder clearfix thumb listing"><img src="http://www.umiteacher.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/179694082-436x356.jpg" class="attachment-blog_thumbnail size-blog_thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="179694082" /></a>
				
				<div class="post_title_area">
										<div class="blogtitles  nodate"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.umiteacher.com/a-new-year-to-seek-god-in-christian-education/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A New Year to Seek God in Christian Education">A New Year to Seek God in Christian Education</a></h2>
						<p class="postmeta"><a href="http://www.umiteacher.com/a-new-year-to-seek-god-in-christian-education/#respond" class="commentslink" >Comments (0)</a><span>|</span><a href="http://www.umiteacher.com/a-new-year-to-seek-god-in-christian-education/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A New Year to Seek God in Christian Education"  class="">Read more</a></p>


						<div class="entry-content  entry-excerpt">

							<p>by Beverly Moore Do not remember the former things, or consider the things of old. I am about to do a new thing; now it springs forth, do you not perceive it? (from Isaiah 43:18&ndash;19, NRSV) A new year brings with it all the possibilities and hope of each new day. It is a time&#8230;</p>
